16/03/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The BiH House of Representatives on Monday (15 March) approved the appointment of Nikola Radovanovic as the first state-level defence minister, following verification of his candidacy by the Office of the High Representative. 
Lawmakers also approved the appointment of two deputy defence ministers, Enes Becirbasic and Marina Pendes. 
Radovanovic says his priority is meeting criteria for admission to NATO's Partnership for Peace programme.
Also Monday, Serbian Deputy Prime Minister Miroljub Labus visited Sarajevo and called for stronger bilateral ties with BiH. 
He said the two countries could assist each other in European integration and provide new momentum for regional co-operation.
In other news, the reunification of Mostar was officially proclaimed Monday, following the abolition of the previous six municipalities. 
High Representative Paddy Ashdown stressed that nine years after the war ended, the city finally has one mayor, a single budget and a single city administration. 
(OHR Sources, Nezavisne novine - 16/03/04; RTRS, PBS BiH, AFP, Reuters, Federal TV - 15/03/04)
